{% set section = {
  title: 'Validation errors',
  id: 'validation-errors'
} %}

<section aria-describedby="{{section.id}}">
  <h2 id="{{section.id}}">
    {{section.title}}
  </h2>
  <p>
    When a form cannot be submitted due to validation errors, those errors should be announced to a screenreader. When a validation error appears on the page, make sure it is the next thing which is announced and make sure that it makes sense.
  </p>
  
  <h3 id="how-to-check-{{section.id}}">
    How to check<span class="at-visually-hidden">: {{section.title}}</span>
  </h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Fill in a form component incorrectly</li>
    <li>Progress until the validation error appears</li>
    <li>Once the error loads, wait for the screen reader to stop talking and observe whether it announced that there was an error</li>
    <li>Press <span class="at-keys">Insert + T</span> to see if the title announces an error</li>
    <li>Press <span class="at-keys">F</span> to move through the form fields and see if it obvious which field caused the error</li>
    <li>Observe whether the field which caused the error explains how to fix it</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 id="what-to-check-{{section.id}}">
    What to check<span class="at-visually-hidden">: {{section.title}}</span>
  </h3>
  <p>
    Confirm that:
    <ul>
      <li>when validation errors occur, the screenreader announced to the user that there is an error</li>
      <li>
        the title of the page changes to indicate there is an error, for example: <span class="at-keys">Error:&nbsp;Your&nbsp;details</span>
      </li>
      <li>it is clear from the screenreader which field caused the error and how to fix it</li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <h3 id="observations-{{section.id}}">
    Observations<span class="at-visually-hidden">: {{section.title}}</span>
  </h3>
  {{- observations | safe -}}
</section>